<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-SONICS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS WIN WITHOUT SHAQ
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It takes a lot of mortals to make up for the loss
of one superstar. Fortunately for the Los Angeles Lakers, Superman
has Superfriends.
</P>
<P>
   With Shaquille O'Neal on the bench for a second straight game,
the Lakers turned to the superhero-by-committee strategy Monday
night and pulled out a dramatic 106-103 overtime victory over the
Seattle SuperSonics before 18,997 at Staples Center.
</P>
<P>
   Glen Rice hit a buzzer-beating 23-footer between Gary Payton and
Jelani McCoy at the end of regulation to tie the score at 94 and
force the extra period.
</P>
<P>
   Once there, the Lakers (65-13) got clutch shooting from Kobe
Bryant, a huge 3-pointer from Rick Fox and a game-sealing dunk from
A.C. Green to pull out the victory and take the season series
against the Sonics, their possible first-round playoff opponent,
3-1.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wow, what a game,'' coach Phil Jackson said. ``Glen hitting a
shot, big one in the corner, finally getting the offense rolling a
little bit in the second half.''
</P>
<P>
   That again proved difficult without the presence of O'Neal,
resting a sprained left ankle for a second straight game. But
Bryant overcame a horrible start to finish with a game-high 33
points on 13-of-28 shooting, and Rice added 28 points on 7-of-18
shooting to prove they can indeed win without their MVP.
</P>
<P>
   Until Monday, they were 0-2 without O'Neal.
</P>
<P>
   Even better, they did it with a huge contribution from the
recently slumping Rice. The Lakers had blown a 13-point lead to
open the fourth quarter and were down 94-92 with 1.4 seconds left.
Rice took the inbounds pass in the corner and hit from 23 feet with
time expiring, and the arena erupted as Rice was hugged by a scrum
of fans at courtside.
</P>
<P>
   ``I knew it was going in,'' Rice said. ``It had the arch and
everything, the follow-through. Everything was perfect. It's sweet,
and those are the things you cherish, cherish for a lifetime
there.''
</P>
<P>
   Rice finished 7 for 18 from the field after a slow start and
added nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's definitely a little lift for me,'' he said. ``I like to
try and do anything I can to get this team a win. And the guys
really were looking for me. They realized I had it going a little
bit. I just thank God I was able to hit the shot.''
</P>
<P>
   Shammond Williams led the Sonics with 28 points off the bench,
and put a brief scare into the Lakers. He hit a 3-pointer in the
final 10 seconds of overtime to slice the lead to 104-103, but the
Lakers quickly sealed the game when Rick Fox zipped the inbounds
pass to Green, who caught the ball behind the defense and hit a
breakaway slam dunk.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers have already sealed the best record in the NBA, but
with four games left, they're trying to find their way without
O'Neal. They were routed by the San Antonio Spurs on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think they wanted to step up and play like they believe in
themselves tonight, and they felt good about themselves,'' Jackson
said.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, these teams are on a collision course to meet again
in two weeks, in the first round of the playoffs. The Sonics
dropped to 1 games behind the Sacramento Kings in the battle for
the seventh and eighth seeds in the West
</P>
<P>
   otherwise known as the battle to avoid the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   Both teams have had some success against the Lakers this season,
but in choosing an opponent for the playoffs, Jackson noted that
since Sacramento ``has been befuddling the Lakers, Seattle seems to
be a better team for us right off the bat.''
</P>
<P>
   It didn't look that way for most of Monday's game.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers shot 28.3 percent in the first half but managed to
find a flow in the third quarter when Bryant snapped out of a
shooting funk to hit 7 of 9 shots, for 16 points. That led the
Lakers to a 34-point quarter, and 59.1 percent shooting - their
best period of the night - as they opened a 73-60 lead to head into
the fourth.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
