   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   BRITAIN-LIPSTADT _ LONDON _ Spot coverage of the verdict in the
case of author David Irving, who is suing Emory University
professor Deborah Lipstadt and her publisher Penguin Books for
libel over assertions made about him in her 1994 book, ``Denying
the Holocaust: The Growing Assault on Truth and Memory.''
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (l) Lifestyle categories.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   ELTONJOHN-ART _ NEW YORK _ The High Museum got such a big bang
out of premiering their plans in New York City for the Norman
Rockwell show in Atlanta last fall, they're doing it again for
their big show of fall 2000. This year, it's a high tea at the St.
Regis Hotel, to announce their exhibit of 400 works from Elton
John's collection of 20th century photography. As Sir Elton will be
there, so will we. (Dollar, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   TINA-TURNER _ ATLANTA _ Tina Turner's ``Farewell'' tour hits
Atlanta tonight, making it a good time to mark her supposed last
performances in the United States with a fun ``Why We'll Miss
Tina''career retrospective. Which may include a Tina Turner doll.
(SoMurray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   FURNITURE-SHOW HIGH POINT, N.C. _ Two of America's leading
celebrity interior designers _ HGTV's Chris Madden and Joe Ruggiero
_ raised the curtain on their own collections of furniture at the
world's largest wholesale market. Madden, in a line for Basset,
introduced furnishings and accessories inspired by the getaways
she's designed for clients such as Oprah Winfrey, Katie Couric and
Toni Morrison. Ruggiero teamed up with Norwalk Furniture to unveil
a streamlined group of furniture, fabrics and accents that can be
used throughout any room in the house. The two, seen weekly by some
62 million households, are among the growing number of celebs
branding their names on collections in the highly competitive home
furnishings industry. (Flanders, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   CHAIRS _ ATLANTA _ The Metro Atlanta Furniture Bank no longer
simply cherishes its future; it's accessorizing it, too. The
nonprofit organization, which provides furniture to the needy, is
sponsoring its sixth annual fund-raiser for which local and
national artists and interior designers take an unfinished chair
frame and get really creative with it. The chairs are then
auctioned off at a gala. Event advance. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Thursday, April 13.
</P>
<P>
   HOMEGARDEN-REVIEW _ Four mini book reviews two gardening and two
home: ``Southern Living Landscape Book'', ``Wildflowers of
Georgia,'' ``Inspiration, Decoration: Starting Points for Stylish
Rooms,'' and ``Better Homes and Gardens Flea Market
Decorating.''(Reed, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed for Thursday, April 13.
</P>
