<HEADER>
A3392 &Cx1f; taf-z
u i BC-BRITAIN-HOLOCAUSTSUIT     04-11 0618
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRITAIN-HOLOCAUSTSUIT-(TRIM)-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HISTORIAN'S HOLOCAUST LIBEL SUIT DISMISSED BY JUDGE IN LONDON 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: This early version will be updated as needed) 
 By CHRISTOPHER S. WREN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   David Irving, a British historian who minimized the tragedy of
the Holocaust, ``misrepresented and manipulated historical
evidence,'' a judge in London ruled Tuesday in throwing out
Irving's libel suit against a U.S. scholar who had accused him of
distorting what occurred in Nazi Germany.
</P>
<P>
   The British historian, David Irving, 62, sued Deborah Lipstadt,
a history professor at Emory University in Atlanta, and Penguin
Books, which published her book in Britain six years ago.
</P>
<P>
   In the book, ``Denying the Holocaust: The Growing Assault on
Truth and Memory,'' Lipstadt described Irving as ``one of the most
dangerous spokespersons for Holocaust denial,'' who played down
Adolph Hitler's responsibility for the slaughter of millions of
Jews.
</P>
<P>
   Irving has not denied that Jews died in Nazi custody, but he
contended that far fewer were murdered than was widely accepted and
said that none died in the notorious gas chambers of Auschwitz. He
argued that Lipstadt's book made it difficult to find publishers
for his writings.
</P>
<P>
   But after presiding over the libel trial for more than eight
weeks, Judge Charles Gray ruled against Irving Tuesday, calling him
``anti-Semitic and racist'' and ``a right-wing pro-Nazi
polemicist.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It appears to me to be incontrovertible that Irving qualifies
as a Holocaust denier,'' Gray said, underscoring what the
historian's critics have said for years. ``Not only has he denied
the existence of gas chambers at Auschwitz and asserted that no Jew
was gassed there, he has done so on frequent occasions and
sometimes in the most offensive terms.''
</P>
<P>
   (BEGIN OPTIONAL TRIM)
</P>
<P>
   Gray also said that Irving was content to mix with neo-fascists
and seemed to share many of their racist and anti-Semitic
prejudices.
</P>
<P>
   ``The charges which I have found substantially true include the
charges that Irving has for his own ideological reasons
persistently and deliberately misrepresented and manipulated
historical evidence,'' Gray said.
</P>
<P>
   (END OPTIONAL TRIM)
</P>
<P>
   Irving described the decision against him as ``perverse'' and
said he would appeal. Gray has yet to rule on who must bear the
legal costs of the trial, but he indicated that Irving would have
to pay most of the defense team's costs, which could exceed $3
million.
</P>
<P>
   Irving enjoyed an advantage in suing Lipstadt in a British court
rather than an American one. In British libel law, the burden of
proof lies on the defendants, in this case Lipstadt and Penguin
Books, while in a U.S. court the responsibility rests with the
plaintiff.
</P>
<P>
   The trial's implications were considered so significant that the
Israeli government offered the unpublished handwritten memoirs of
Adolph Eichmann to buttress Lipstadt's defense. Eichmann, the Nazi
official who organized the deportation of millions of Jews to death
camps during World War II, was captured by Israeli agents in
Argentina and, after a highly publicized trial in Jerusalem, was
hanged in 1962.
</P>
<P>
   Gray said Tuesday that Irving failed to show that Lipstadt's
book had damaged his reputation.
</P>
<P>
   Jewish groups that have worked to preserve the memory of the
Holocaust expressed satisfaction with the verdict.
</P>
<P>
   ``David Irving's career as a historian is over,'' the Simon
Wiesenthal Center in Los Angeles said in a statement. ``Today's
decision definitely places Irving where he belongs _ not as a
historian but as a leading apologist for those who seek to
whitewash the most heinous crime in human history.''
</P>
</TEXT>
