million over five years to states that adopt mandatory sentences
for firearms convictions. This Republican-sponsored bill, which is
expected to draw bipartisan support, is modeled after Virginia's
Project Exile program. Democrats are likely to counter with their
own non-binding measure to pressure the House-Senate conferees to
deal with the stalled gun control bill. Will wrap in the
