   MARKET (New York) _ At 1:40 p.m., the Nasdaq composite index was
down 37 points. The Dow Jones industrial average was up 147 points
and the S&AMP;P 500 was up 4 points. Treasury prices were lower. Crude
oil was slightly higher, at $24.10 a barrel. European stock markets
were lower: London down 2.66 percent and Frankfurt down 0.75
percent. In Asia, the Nikkei closed down 0.47 percent; the Hang
Seng ended down 2.15 percent. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
