<P>
   CENSUS _ WASHINGTON _ Census officials appear unlikely to meet
Tuesday's goal of increasing American participation in the
once-a-decade head count. Federal officials do not expect to meet
their target of a 70 percent mail-back rate for census
questionnaires, and may not match the 65 percent rate from 1990,
meaning the 2000 census will continue a 30-year trend of each count
being more expensive and less accurate than the last. (Holmes, Cox
News Service). 18.
