   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DRUG-LIFELINE (Northfield, Vt.) _ In response to a two-week-old
blitz of advertisements funded by the pharmaceutical industry,
Vermont's governor is making an effort to openly advertise Canada's
lower prescription drug prices, hoping to ``embarrass the U.S.
Congress'' into initiating price controls. By Ellen Barry. 1270
words. PHOTO (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOLS-TESTING (Boston) _ One of the nation's most visible
symbols of the high-stakes testing movement, Massachusetts is
carving out a new title for itself: Backlash capital. As students
start the third round of MCAS testing, nearly a dozen protests are
planned. By Doreen Iudica Vigue and Beth Daley. 860 words.
</P>
