   &UR; COMMENTARY (k) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   WALKER-COLUMN (Miami) -- After the energy that followed the
Miami-Dade mayor's threat to disregard federal law 13 days ago, the
reality has set in that Elian Gonzalez's transfer back to his
father -- and Cuba -- is a done deal. By Adrian Walker.
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) _ It's been a tough month for ABC
News. By Thomas Oliphant.
</P>
<P>
   LANGUAGE-COLUMN (Undated) -- When idioms stop making sense. By
Jan Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HEALTH/SCIENCE (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCI-SNOWY-OWLS (Undated) _ Snowy owls often tarry at wintry New
England barrier beaches, saltmarshes and airports. Now scientists
using tiny transmitters are studying the owls' movements and
lifestyle. By Mark Wilson 1480 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-TOSCHES (New York) _ Nick Tosches has just come out with
