raided the charter company that operated the Learjet that crashed
last October while carrying Payne Stewart, looking for criminal
violations of federal transportation safety laws. The agents seized
boxes of documents from three buildings and four aircraft belonging
to Sunjet Aviation, at Orlando Sanford International Airport. By
