   RITEAID-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Rite Aid, having failed to find
buyers for its PCS Health Systems subsidiary, has announced a plan
to refinance its debt for more than two years, giving it access to
more than $640 million in additional funds. The deal came at a cost
of higher interest rates on some of its borrowings and substantial
dilution for its stockholders. Shares of Rite Aid rose $1.625, to
$7.3125. By Floyd Norris.
