points, to 4,055.90. By the close of trading the index was lower
than at the start of the year, and nearly 20 percent below the peak
reached on March 10. Meanwhile, money continued to move into blue
chip stocks from technology companies that carry much higher price
to earnings ratios. Helped by strong gains in stocks like Alcoa and
Minnesota Mining &AMP; Manufacturing, the Dow Jones industrial average
gained 100.52 points, or 0.9 percent, to 11,287.08. By Kenneth N.
