<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Rings' trailer sets Internet record
 &HT;    By Bob Longino
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   With a helpful push from New Line Cinema, the Internet preview
for the upcoming three-part movie ``The Lord of the Rings'' has set
a record, amassing 1.671 million downloads in one day of the
exclusive online trailer.
</P>
<P>
   Apple Computer, which confirmed the downloads, earlier had
counted roughly 1 million downloads in a day for the trailer for
``Star Wars: Episode 1 _ The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   New Line's marketing team admits it has been working with up to
25 Web fan sites to pump up interest in the trilogy. The first
``Rings'' film _ ``The Fellowship of the Ring'' _ debuts in 2001.
</P>
<P>
   _Bob Longino writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   ON THE WEB
</P>
<P>
   To download the ``Rings'' preview: www.lordoftherings.net
</P>
