<P>
   (NYT16) BUENOS AIRES, Argentina -- April 11, 2000 --
ARGENTINE-EMPANADAS-1 -- Ramon Torres and Cecilia Hermann sell
empanadas at La Cupertina in Buenos Aires. The custom of the
Portenos, the cosmopolitan inhabitants of Buenos Aires, is to down
these hot, hand-held pies for quick lunches, often consuming four
or five as a meal, or two or three as a snack. (Horacio Paone/The
New York Times)
