Renneisen, the new head of the Miss America Organization.
Renneisen, an Atlantic City casino chief who lost his job when the
Claridge Casino and Hotel Corp. filed for bankruptcy last fall,
entered the pageant picture with an agenda that leaves the old
rules intact. ``Miss America is an icon owned by the American
people, and anachronistic and puritanical as it is, a lot of people
want her to be virginal and pure as the driven snow,'' he said.
(Librado Romero/The New York Times)
