r f BC-VENTURE-VENTURE_SFCHR     04-11 0340
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VENTURE-VENTURE </SLUG>
 _ SF CHRON  
 Brience Attracts $200 Million Golden Financing  &HT;     By Peter Sinton 
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
In what could be the largest first-round venture financing of a
startup, GTCR Golden Rauner of Chicago announced yesterday that it
has invested $200 million in Brience Inc. of San Francisco.
<P>
   The company, whose name is short for broadband experience, is
developing software that allows big companies to deliver e-commerce
solutions through a variety of devices such as personal digital
assistants, cell phones and TV set-top boxes. Brience's technology
also will let companies personalize access by providing premium
bandwidth to their best customers.
</P>
<P>
   The company was founded last month by Rod McGeary, former co-CEO
of KPMG Consulting LLC, and Keyur Patel, former chief strategist
for e-business at KPMG. McGeary is CEO and chairman of Brience,
Patel its chief strategist.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think this is the largest first-round found  &LR; financing
ever,'' said Patel.
</P>
<P>
   ``Two hundred million would be an exceedingly large round,''
said Tamar Zemel, a spokesperson for VentureOne, a San Francisco
research firm that tracks venture capital investments. ``Last year,
the median first-round investment was $6 million, and the median
size of all investment rounds was $7.5 million.''
</P>
<P>
   Out of 2,969 U.S. venture financings last year, only four
companies received more than $200 million, and all of these  &LR; were
later-round investments. For example, CarsDirect.com of Culver City
received $280 million in third-round financing; Webvan of Foster
City raised $275 million; Spectrasite Holdings of Cary, N.C.,
raised $231 million; and Corvis Corp. of Columbia, Md., raised $216
million.
</P>
<P>
   Brience expects two Fortune 500 companies to begin testing its
content delivery software next month. GTCR of Chicago, which
manages more than $4.5 billion in private equity investments,
focuses on e-business and other information technology
opportunities.
</P>
