r s BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LAD     04-11 0745
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-NOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PEREZ FRUSTRATED WITH DODGERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEVE DILBECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO -- Carlos Perez hasn't exactly been left hanging,
but he is growing increasingly frustrated over his tenuous role
with the Dodgers.
</P>
<P>
   With ace Kevin Brown scheduled to on the 15-day disabled list,
manager Davey Johnson said he is ``leaning'' towards giving the
struggling Perez -- who was sent down to Triple-A Albuquerque on
Friday but remains with the club -- the start Thursday against the
Giants.
</P>
<P>
   It's all but official Perez will be added back to the roster and
start, but he's yet to hear it.
</P>
<P>
   ``This thing is not going to make me crazy,'' Perez said.
``There are lots of places to go. I don't want to go anywhere, but
I'm getting tired of this b-------.
</P>
<P>
   ``They probably don't trust my stuff. Then I don't want to be
here anymore. I don't want it to be like last year.''
</P>
<P>
   Coming off a dismal season (2-10, 7.43 ERA) and a rough first
start (4.2 innings, eight runs, five earned, seven hits) this year,
Perez is not going to attract much interest -- he has two years and
$12.6 million left on his contract.
</P>
<P>
   Dodgers general manager said Perez was being given a
``reprieve'' with a second start.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is an opportunity for Carlos to step up and hopefully
turn a corner,'' Malone said. ``This is a positive reprieve, and
hopefully we'll get the results we're looking for.''
</P>
<P>
   Perez, however, thinks the Dodgers have reacted too quickly to
his lone start against the Expos.
</P>
<P>
   ``One start?'' Perez said. ``They can't see anything. I don't
know what they're trying to do. If they want me to pitch, they'd
better let me alone and let me pitch my f------ game.''
</P>
<P>
   Johnson will be looking for quick results in a second start.
</P>
<P>
   ``I need him,'' he said. ``I need that depth. Clubs we face are
loaded with left-handed batters. But I need him to pitch like he
did a couple of years ago.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Malone: ``He knows where he's supposed to be -- he's
supposed to be one of our five starters. But we also have to win
games. If it means sending Carlos out to get more work, that's what
we'll do. We want to do whatever we can to get him back on track.''
</P>
<P>
   KARROS OUT: Gary Sheffield (sprained right ankle) made it into
the lineup, but Eric Karros (strained lower back) did not.
</P>
<P>
   Karros said his back knotted up during the team's lengthy wait
at Shea Stadium after Sunday's game was snowed out.
</P>
<P>
   ``It just locked up on me, while we sat around and waited,''
Karros said.
</P>
<P>
   Karros reported some slight progress Tuesday, but gave it the
day-to-day routine. He was still moving very stiffly after the
game.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's eased a little bit, but he's in no shape to play,''
Johnson said. ``He can't move or bend over.''
</P>
<P>
   Geronimo Berroa, normally an outfielder, started for Karros and
took his fifth spot in the lineup.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson said Sheffield was at Pac Bell Park by 7:30 a.m. to
treat the ankle, but it wasn't certain he would start until game
time.
</P>
<P>
   TIDBITS: Johnson won't commit to whom he'll add to the rotation
for Saturday's start against the Reds, but said it would involve a
``young pitcher or two.'' Left-hander Jeff Williams was added to
the roster Tuesday to take the place of right-hander Gregg Olson
(strained forearm) and will likely start Saturday. If the Dodgers
call up a starter from Albuquerque, it is expected to be right-
hander Eric Gagne. ... Despite going to Los Angeles to have his
finger examined on Monday and the team returning there on Friday,
Brown joined the Dodgers in San Francisco on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   DODGERS VS. GIANTS
</P>
<P>
   TIME: 7:05 p.m. at Pacific Bell Park
</P>
<P>
   TV/RADIO: Fox Sports Net 2, XTRA-1150 and KWKW-1330 (Spanish)
</P>
<P>
   STARTING PITCHERS: Darren Dreifort (0-1, 3.60 ERA) vs. Joe
Nathan (0-0, 1.29).
</P>
<P>
   DODGERS (4-3) UPDATE: With Kevin Brown out, the Dodgers are
again lookin g for a big outing from Dreifort. Eric Karros
(strained back) is also ex pected to remain out. Geroninmo Berroa
filled for Karros Tuesday, but Da ve Hansen will likely get the nod
against a right-hander. Kevin Elster h ad now scored at least one
run in all six of his starts.
