<HEADLINE>
TROJANS TO SIGN POINT GUARD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC is expected to sign just one basketball player
today after losing out on a pair of recruits this week. Today is
the first day players can sign national letters-of-intent.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans will sign 5-foot-10 point guard Robert Hutchinson
from Okaloosa-Walton Junior College in Niceville, Fla. Hutchinson
averaged 13.5 points, 7.2 assists and 2.6 rebounds per game this
season. He will enter USC as a sophomore.
</P>
<P>
   The player USC coveted most - shooting guard Travis Hanour of
Laguna Beach High - selected Arizona on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's made the decision (not to go to USC),'' Laguna Beach
coach Bret Fleming said.
</P>
<P>
   Hanour committed to USC in late February but changed his mind
and began visiting other schools in March.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans also lost out on Hanour's teammate, 6-foot-9 forward
Chris Manker, who has committed to Oregon State. USC still has
three scholarships available.
</P>
</TEXT>
